# Push narration style (routine commits/pushes)

The maintainer does not want the boilerplate security/carve-out status line on
routine code pushes. For all future mods:

- After a **routine** `git commit` / `git push`, **do not** narrate lines like
  "No security/carve-out triggers, so this was a routine push" or
  "no triggers apply". Just report what was committed/pushed (commit hash,
  branch, files) and move on.
- This is a **communication-only** preference. It does **not** weaken the
  security gate.

## Gate logic is unchanged

- `security-git-push-gate.mdc` and `production-carveouts.mdc` still apply in full.
- If a **real trigger** appears in the staged/added set (e.g. `.env`/secrets,
  `lib/auth/**`, `middleware.ts`, `lib/trust/**`, `lib/aihsafe/**`,
  `prisma/schema.prisma` user/session changes, destructive `scripts/**`,
  `never0`/`sec/`/`security/`, or a `TaiKos` carve-out), still **stop and
  prompt** for explicit yes/no before committing/pushing.
- The suppression only covers the *narration* on pushes that did **not** hit a
  trigger.
